cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new pre-training scheme for U-net based image segmentation, specifically applied to the problem of segmenting the optic disc from fundus photographs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the transfer of learned features between tasks, which suggests a potential application of transfer learning and deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The use of medical images also suggests a potential fit for cs.MM (Multimedia) and the use of neural networks suggests a potential fit for cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
